<Author>elmarko
<Content>A GEM OF A HOTEL IN MADRID!!! Location, location, location. Absolutely fantastic. Right in the Salamanca district near fine shops and restaurants. Also convenient to two Metro stations within 2 blocks each way. Simply one of the finest hotels we've ever stayed at in Europe! Spent 5 wonderful days in Madrid, and the service, professionalism, and attention at the Adler could not have been better. The staff is superior with one of the warmest, friendlest attitudes of any place we've ever visited in the WORLD! Save the $$$ you would spend for a room at the Ritz and stay here. The rooms are extraordinarily large for Europe with double sinks in the marble bathroom, plus ALL ROOMS ARE SOUNDPROOFED SO YOU DON'T HEAR A PEEP! The restaurant in the hotel was a little pricey, but that was completely insignificant. I can assure you that if you stay at the Adler you'll come away saying the same wonderful things I've experienced. There really wasn't anything to criticize. This place is a real find! 
