<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Wonderful Hotel After I had already decided on staying at the Hotel Adler, I read some of the disappointing reviews and was a little hesitant about staying at the hotel. However, I found all of the negative comments to be 100% false. The hotel was extremely clean and beautiful. The staff was courteous and helpful in all situations. I arrived earlier than I expected. However, the room I requested (one on a high floor) was provided without any wait. When I returned in the afternoon, a large fresh fruit place (along with a message from the manager) was in the room. My room faced the busy street, but with the windows and shutters closed, I did not hear a thing at night. During my entire four night stay, I did not encounter one problem. The hotel is small (only 48 rooms) and if you are looking for an active lobby bar, this is not the place. However, the room was large (queen bed with a large desk, small table and two chairs for a sitting area), and sunny with the windows open. The bathroom was large (altough the counter space was minimal). The hotel is also very convenient to wonderful shopping. I booked directly through their website and found that to be the best price. I highly recommend this hotel for a relaxing, comfortable stay in Madrid. 
