<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Well below five star standard This hotel is very expensive and has many positive reviews on Tripadvisor and elsewhere. Therefore I had high expectations for my two night visit...Oh what a let down!On the positive side, the room had quality furniture and a warm and charming design style. It was modern without being cold and minimalist. The bathroom was also excellent..well almost...and the staff were friendly and helpful. HOWEVER...This hotel does not deserve five stars and falls well short of the standards required of a property at that level. The problems started when we called room service for a snack at 7pm and were told that the kitchen only opens at 8pm! This was incorrect and there was a minimal service available 24hrs, but the restaurant, where the room service calls are received, was apparently unaware of this...very odd! On another occasion we ordered dinner with wine, which arrived with no wine glasses. This situation continued with items missing from the breakfast order and a yogurt with mould growing on it. It did get so bad I was expecting John Cleese to deliver the next room service order!So other than the room service, what else was wrong?...Our room had no balcony and had a view of the walls surrounding the entrance to the car park. It was very dark with almost no natural light. I asked to change, but was informed that the only other options would either be smaller or would only have twin beds....so we stayed in the gloom!Other issues were the lobby and bar, which were sterile and totally lacking in atmosphere...They remained empty for my entire stay. There was also the shower, which was designed in such a way that it leaked water all over the bathroom floor...I could go on, but the summary is that this is NOT a hotel worthy of five stars or the prices it charges. I would not go back and would strongly recommend that others avoid this place. There are many better options in Madrid. 
