<Content>5 star rating and still not a sanitized bathroom I stayed here on the last leg of my trip after traveling for 3 weeks in Spain. After staying in some places that I thought couldn't even get a 1 star rating, I longed to a few days of relaxing in a five star hotel. First impression, yes, this is for the sophisticated, well heeled traveler or savvy business professional. I walked in in flip flops and a duffel bag and those around me were in Prada and Chanel. I couldn't wait to get to my room and soak in a bubble bath. I thought I had finally left all those other hotels where cleanliness was dubious at best. When I walked into my room it was indeed, very luxorious in every detail from the fine furnishings to the expensive fabrics on the bed and the curtains. Yippee, I thought!! Finally, a slice of heaven. I ripped off my clothes and headed straight for my bubble bath only to find in my 5 star hotel, two very unwanted pieces of hair which I will not describe further, but they clearly didn't come from me or the cleaning person's head. Yuck!! As an American, we have OSHA regulations and hygiene in most hotels is a given. In Spain, I found so many hotels fell short in cleanliness and this hotel, sadly, proved to follow suit. At $400+ a night, I EXPECTED a properly sanitized bathroom. I still took my bubble bath anyway, but my lasting impression of this hotel will always be a bad visual of p***** hair. 
