<Content>This is a great hotel This is a great boutique hotel. I stayed there last July during a heat-wave. But unlike most hotels in Europe during the summer, the heat was not a problem. The air-conditioning worked perfectly. Beautiful rooms. Comfortable beds, large living area, large bathrooms. I was there on business and was able to work in my room for hours without any problems (although, they did not have high-speed). The staff at the front desk was excellent. I had an emergency dental problem when I was there and they found me dentist that spoke English and was open on Saturday (amazing feat for the summer in Spain). The food in the restaurant was amazing. I loved dining there. The hotel is located in the heart of the shopping district and very close to the museums. The next time I'm in Madrid, I plan on staying there again. 
